LAGOS – Some members of the All progressives Congress (APC) in Ekiti State have defected to the Action Democratic Party (ADP). The APC members defected yesterday during the flag-off campaign of the ADP governorship candidate Erelu Kemi Elebute-Halle at Ode Ekiti Gbonyin local government area of the state. Speaking to newsmen, the Director-General DG of the Erelu Elebute-Halle campaign organization, Hon. Musa Arogundade expressed confidence in the ADP candidate to emerge victoriously in the forthcoming gubernatorial election. -Advertisement- “Today, we want to flag off our campaign at Gbonyin Local Government and by God’s grace, we believe that the votes of the Ekiti people must count. We believe that the people of Ekiti state will vote for us, most especially the women of Ekiti state.” “We are here now, we have been to the palace and we have encouraged every citizen of Ekiti State to go out on that day and vote, not just vote, to go out and vote for us. The only female contesting for the governorship in the state stands out amongst the other contenders. Women support their gender and it is logical that they will support her,” he said. The Chairman of the party at the local government and the Youth leader of the party, Akinlade Akinbode and Adewumi Adeolu, in separate interviews, described the party’s flagbearer as “one who has the interest of Ekiti at heart”. Recall that Ode Ekiti is the home town of Hon. Idowu Afuye, the deputy governorship candidate recently defected to the APC. Some of the defectors expressed confidence in “the ability of the ADP candidate to turn things around in the state.